  "conclusion": [
    "On unperturbed systems FGMRES adds one full-KKT application per iteration and is not a general speed win.",
    "When perturbations are active, K_delta/K_delta and K/K_delta are observably different algorithms and both can alter the Ipopt trajectory.",
    "The K/K_delta mode reaches the unperturbed full-KKT residual and can avoid perturbation-driven outer iterations, but must remain opt-in because it changes the accepted direction semantics."
  ]
